---
---

<section class="features" id="features" aria-labelledby="features-heading">
  <header class="features-head" data-animate>
    <p class="kicker">Platform</p>
    <h2 id="features-heading">Three layers. One workspace.</h2>
    <p class="sub">
      Most teams use separate tools for tracking work, running agents, and capturing what they learn. Amprealize is built to keep all three in sync.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="bento" data-animate style="transition-delay: 60ms">
    <!-- Pillar 1 – Work management -->
    <article class="tile tile--pillar pressable">
      <div class="tile-icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" width="20" height="20">
          <rect x="3.5" y="4" width="17" height="16" rx="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75"></rect>
          <path d="M3.5 9h17" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          <path d="M8.5 4v5M15.5 4v5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          <path d="M7 14h2.5M7 17.5h5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          <path d="M14 13.5l1.5 1.5 3-3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="tile-body">
        <h3>Manage work the way you already know</h3>
        <p>Boards, projects, and task queues that keep humans and agents moving on the same backlog — without a separate tool for each.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Pillar 2 – Agent teammates -->
    <article class="tile tile--pillar pressable">
      <div class="tile-icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" width="20" height="20">
          <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75"></circle>
          <path d="M3 19c0-3.314 2.686-6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          <circle cx="17" cy="10" r="2.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="2.5 1.5"></circle>
          <path d="M17 13c2.209 0 4 1.791 4 4v1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          <path d="M13.5 16.5l1.5 1.5 3-3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="tile-body">
        <h3>Agents that contribute, not just respond</h3>
        <p>Assign work to AI agents alongside your team. They pick up tasks, surface results on the board, and hand off to a human when judgment is needed.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Pillar 3 – Behavior library -->
    <article class="tile tile--pillar pressable">
      <div class="tile-icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" width="20" height="20">
          <path d="M8 2.5 13 5.75v4.5L8 13.5 3 10.25v-4.5L8 2.5Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
          <path d="M13 5.75l8 4.75v5l-8 4.75" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
          <path d="M8 13.5v8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="tile-body">
        <h3>Save what works — not just what ran</h3>
        <p>Every good agent run can become a versioned behavior your whole team reuses. Ship faster because you stop re-solving the same problems.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Supporting tiles -->
    <article class="tile tile--sm pressable">
      <div class="tile-icon tile-icon--sm" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" width="18" height="18">
          <path d="M12 4v4M12 16v4M4 12h4M16 12h4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3.25" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75"></circle>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="tile-body">
        <h3>Trace to insight</h3>
        <p>Surface behavioral patterns from agent runs automatically. No manual logging required.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="tile tile--sm tile--accent pressable">
      <div class="tile-icon tile-icon--sm tile-icon--invert" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" width="18" height="18">
          <path d="M6 7h12M6 12h8M6 17h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          <path d="M9 4.5h6l1.5 2v13H7.5v-13L9 4.5Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="tile-body">
        <h3>MCP-native</h3>
        <p>Every action has a tool call equivalent. Automation and audit are built in from day one.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="tile tile--sm pressable">
      <div class="tile-icon tile-icon--sm" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" width="18" height="18">
          <path d="M8 6.5h8v11H8v-11Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
          <path d="M10 9h4M10 12h4M10 15h3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="tile-body">
        <h3>CLI &amp; VS Code</h3>
        <p>Fits the loop you already like. No context switching to see what your agents shipped.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .features {
    width: 100%;
    padding-top: var(--landing-section-y, clamp(48px, 7vw, 88px));
  }

  .features-head {
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
  }

  .kicker {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: var(--font-bold);
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .features-head h2 {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 1.6vw + 0.4rem, 1.7rem);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    font-weight: var(--font-bold);
  }

  .sub {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  /* ── Bento grid ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .bento {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    grid-template-rows: auto auto;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .tile {
    border-radius: var(--radius-2xl);
    border: 1px solid rgba(70, 108, 140, 0.18);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px) saturate(140%);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px) saturate(140%);
    padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-5);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    align-content: start;
    transition:
      transform var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-spring-gentle),
      border-color var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out-quart),
      background var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out-quart);
    will-change: transform;
  }

  .tile:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--color-border-hover);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86);
  }

  /* Pillars: wider, more prominent */
  .tile--pillar {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    align-items: start;
    padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-5);
  }

  /* Supporting tiles: smaller */
  .tile--sm {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    align-items: start;
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
  }

  .tile--accent {
    border-color: rgba(34, 118, 210, 0.3);
    background: rgba(34, 118, 210, 0.07);
  }

  .tile--accent:hover {
    background: rgba(34, 118, 210, 0.12);
  }

  .tile-icon {
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    background: rgba(34, 118, 210, 0.09);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .tile-icon--sm {
    width: 34px;
    height: 34px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }

  .tile-icon--invert {
    background: var(--color-accent);
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
  }

  .tile-body {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .tile h3 {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: var(--font-semibold);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .tile--sm h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .tile p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .bento {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .bento {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
